ggplot2

Подготовим данные:

library(data.table)
library(ggplot2)

source("analyze_age.R")
DT <- data.table(data)
edu_age <- DT[!(iDedu_level %in% c(1, 2)), .N, by = c("iDedu_level", 
    "iDage_group")]

Зададим эстетики:

ggplot(data = edu_age, aes(x = factor(iDedu_level), y = N, fill = iDage_group))

нарисуем точки

ggplot(data = edu_age, aes(x = factor(iDedu_level), y = N, color = iDage_group)) + 
    geom_point(size = 3)

убрать NA

edu_age <- edu_age[!is.na(iDedu_level)]
edu_age <- edu_age[!is.na(iDage_group)]
ggplot(data = edu_age, aes(x = factor(iDedu_level), y = N, color = iDage_group)) + 
    geom_point(size = 3)

меняем на столбики

ggplot(data = edu_age, aes(x = factor(iDedu_level), y = N, fill = iDage_group)) + 
    geom_bar(stat = "identity")

Можно нарисовать график и по исходным данным, но это приводит к повышенной нагрузке при отрисовке графиков, а вы теряете полноценный контроль над процессом. Отлаживать графики, которые сами себе что-то вычисляют - труднее чем те, которые только рисуют.

ggplot(data = DT, aes(x = factor(iDedu_level), fill = iDage_group)) + 
    geom_bar()

столбики рядом

ggplot(data = edu_age, aes(x = factor(iDedu_level), y = N, fill = iDage_group)) + 
    geom_bar(stat = "identity", position = position_dodge())

переподготовим данные

Перекодируем уровни с помощью превращения переменной в фактор.

DT[, `:=`(edu, factor(iDedu_level))]
levels(DT$edu) <- c("", "", "школа", "бакалавр", "магистр", "доктор", 
    "доктор")
edu_age <- DT[!(edu %in% c("", NA)), .N, by = c("edu", "iDage_group")]
setnames(edu_age, "iDage_group", "age")
edu_age <- edu_age[!is.na(age)]

ggplot(data = edu_age, aes(x = edu, y = N, fill = age)) + geom_bar(stat = "identity", 
    position = position_dodge())

подпишем горизонтальную ось

ggplot(data = edu_age, aes(x = edu, y = N, fill = age)) + geom_bar(stat = "identity", 
    position = position_dodge()) + labs(x = "Образование")

несколько геомов

ggplot(data = edu_age, aes(x = edu, y = N, fill = age, label = N)) + 
    geom_bar(stat = "identity", position = position_dodge()) + labs(x = "Образование") + 
    geom_text(position = position_dodge(width = 1))

подвинем лейблы повыше, шрифт поменьше

ggplot(data = edu_age, aes(x = edu, y = N, fill = age, label = N)) + 
    geom_bar(stat = "identity", position = position_dodge(width = 1)) + 
    labs(x = "Образование") + geom_text(position = position_dodge(width = 1), 
    vjust = -0.6, size = 3)

раздвинем верхнюю ось

ggplot(data = edu_age, aes(x = edu, y = N, fill = age, label = N)) + 
    geom_bar(stat = "identity", position = position_dodge(width = 1)) + 
    labs(x = "Образование") + geom_text(position = position_dodge(width = 1), 
    vjust = -0.6, size = 3) + scale_y_continuous(limits = c(0, 1600))

поправим ширину

ggplot(data = edu_age, aes(x = edu, y = N, fill = age, label = N)) + 
    geom_bar(stat = "identity", position = position_dodge(width = 0.95)) + 
    labs(x = "Образование") + geom_text(position = position_dodge(width = 0.95), 
    vjust = -0.6, size = 3) + scale_y_continuous(limits = c(0, 1600))

посчитаем проценты

edu_age[, `:=`(sum_by_edu, sum(N)), by = edu]
edu_age[, `:=`(share, N/sum_by_edu)]
ggplot(data = edu_age, aes(x = edu, y = share, fill = age, label = N)) + 
    geom_bar(stat = "identity", position = position_dodge(width = 0.95)) + 
    labs(x = "Образование") + geom_text(position = position_dodge(width = 0.95), 
    vjust = -0.6, size = 3) + scale_y_continuous(limits = c(0, max(edu_age$share) + 
    max(edu_age$share) * 0.07))

досчитаем проценты и развернём оси

edu_age[, `:=`(perc, paste0(round(100 * share, 1), "%"))]
ggplot(data = edu_age, aes(x = edu, y = share, fill = age, label = perc)) + 
    geom_bar(stat = "identity", position = position_dodge(width = 0.95)) + 
    labs(x = "Образование") + geom_text(position = position_dodge(width = 0.95), 
    hjust = -0.3, size = 3) + scale_y_continuous(limits = c(0, max(edu_age$share) + 
    max(edu_age$share) * 0.07)) + coord_flip()

а теперь линии

ggplot(data = edu_age, aes(x = edu, y = share, color = age, label = perc, 
    group = age)) + geom_line(stat = "identity") + labs(x = "Образование") + 
    geom_text(hjust = -0.3, size = 3) + scale_y_continuous(limits = c(0, 
    max(edu_age$share) + max(edu_age$share) * 0.07)) + theme_bw()

убираем рамочки и решётку

ggplot(data = edu_age, aes(x = edu, y = share, color = age, label = perc, 
    group = age)) + geom_line(stat = "identity", size = 1) + labs(x = "Образование") + 
    geom_text(hjust = -0.5, size = 3) + scale_y_continuous(limits = c(0, 
    max(edu_age$share) + max(edu_age$share) * 0.07)) + theme_minimal() + 
    theme(axis.title.y = element_blank(), axis.text.y = element_blank(), 
        panel.grid = element_blank())

А теперь посмотрим на тему из пакета ggthemes! (Установите пакет!)

library(ggthemes)
ggplot(data = edu_age, aes(x = edu, y = share, color = age, label = perc, 
    group = age)) + geom_line(stat = "identity", size = 1) + labs(x = "Образование") + 
    geom_text(hjust = -0.5, size = 3) + scale_y_continuous(limits = c(0, 
    max(edu_age$share) + max(edu_age$share) * 0.07)) + theme_wsj()

Посмотрим на линию тренда.

setnames(DT, "Duration__in_seconds_", "time")
ggplot(DT[which(time < 5000)][!is.na(iDage)], aes(x = time, y = iDage)) + 
    geom_point(alpha = 0.3) + geom_smooth(method = "loess") + theme_wsj()

Научимся управлять цветом

ggplot(DT[which(time < 5000)][!is.na(iDage)][!is.na(iDgender)], aes(x = time, 
    y = iDage, color = iDgender)) + geom_point(alpha = 0.3) + theme_wsj() + 
    scale_color_manual(values = c("#FF0000", "green", "blue", "gray")) + 
    theme(legend.title = element_blank())

Научимся сохранять результаты

g <- ggplot(DT[which(time < 5000)][!is.na(iDage)][!is.na(iDgender)], 
    aes(x = time, y = iDage, color = iDgender)) + geom_point(alpha = 0.3) + 
    theme_wsj() + scale_color_manual(values = c("#FF0000", "green", 
    "blue", "gray")) + theme(legend.title = element_blank())
dir.create("output")
## Warning in dir.create("output"): 'output' уже существует
ggsave("output/age_duration.png", g, width = 10, height = 6, unit = "cm")
